 “During this lockdown period, we will freeze your membership automatically and no debit order charge will run for as long as the clubs are closed. There is nothing that you need to do. We will automatically freeze your membership and reinstate your membership and your monthly direct debit when your club re-opens,” the statement read. ALSO READ: SanParks to close all facilities tomorrow following coronavirus lockdown “We are fully supportive of government’s steps to curb the transmission of Covid-19. “We understand the inconvenience this may cause to you and your fitness regime, and will continue to monitor the situation. Your club will reopen as soon as it is safe to do so.”